<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The Valar is the title for all those created by the Illúvitar.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, the Valar are the greatest of the Singers created by Illuvatar.  Melkor, Manwe, Ulmo, Tulkas, Orome, Mandos, etc., were a few of the Valar.  The Maiar were the lesser Singers -- Melian the Maia, Sauron, Balrogs, etc., were examples of Maiar.  All were able to walk with or without bodies.  Manwe is the chief of the Valar, and Varda is his wife.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The first three Istari governed Middle Earth, the last two were bound to Valinor and only briefly stepped foot upon the Western shores of Middle Earth...Near the Realm of Arnor, actually.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
